oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Little Tennessee River
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Bridge across the Little Tennessee River.

It was replaced when they built the Tellico Dam. The Little Tennessee River is a 135-mile (217 km) tributary of the Tennessee River. The Little Tennessee River emerges from the mountains in the present day town of Vonore.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
